<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="272" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1869,2040]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,153,539]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="272" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1869,1895]" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[321,525,1869,1895]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropilosa">
<emphasis box="[321,525,1869,1895]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">Empis nigropilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be a doubtful species. It is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1865" box="[1109,1263,1869,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis box="[1109,1126,1870,1895]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1139,1193,1869,1895]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">hirta</emphasis>
Loew
</taxonomicName>
described from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,241,1905,1931]" name="Georgia" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">Georgia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Loew, H." box="[255,386,1904,1931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" pagination="234 - 242" refId="ref8276" refString="Loew, H. (1865) Ueber einige bei Kutais in Imeretien gefangene Dipteren. Berliner Entomologische Zeitschrift, 9, 234 - 242. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 18650090307" type="journal article" year="1865">Loew 1865</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Syrovatka, O." box="[397,577,1905,1931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" pagination="225 - 278" refId="ref8399" refString="Syrovatka, O. (1991) Revision of H. Loew's and T. Becker's types of Empis s. str. species (Diptera, Empididae) in the Berlin and St Petersburg Museums. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 67, 225 - 278. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnz. 19910670203" type="journal article" year="1991">Syrovátka 1991</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1865" box="[595,726,1905,1931]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis box="[595,726,1905,1931]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">Empis hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in the Caucasus and locally quite common occurring over a broad range of altitudes from submontane area closer the shores of the Black Sea up to 
<quantity box="[1350,1436,1941,1968]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" unit="m" value="1600.0">1600 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kustov, S. Yu. &amp; Shamshev, I. V." box="[159,460,1977,2003]" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" pagination="170 - 184" refId="ref8188" refString="Kustov, S. Yu. &amp; Shamshev, I. V. (2014) A review of dance-flies of the Empis (s. str.) pennipes group of species (Diptera: Empididae) from the Caucasus, with descriptions of five new species. Caucasian Entomological Bulletin, 10, 170 - 184. [in Russian, partly English] https: // doi. org / 10.23885 / 1814 - 3326 - 2014 - 10 - 1 - 170 - 184" type="journal article" year="2014">Kustov &amp; Shamshev 2014</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Syrovatka, O." box="[478,673,1977,2003]" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" pagination="225 - 278" refId="ref8399" refString="Syrovatka, O. (1991) Revision of H. Loew's and T. Becker's types of Empis s. str. species (Diptera, Empididae) in the Berlin and St Petersburg Museums. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 67, 225 - 278. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnz. 19910670203" type="journal article" year="1991">Syrovátka (1991)</bibRefCitation>
re-described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1865" box="[826,911,1977,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis box="[826,843,1978,2003]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[857,911,1977,2003]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and designated the 
<typeStatus box="[1133,1239,1977,2003]" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">lectotype</typeStatus>
, but he compared this species only with 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew. Unfortunately, Syrovatka (1991)" authorityName="Loew. Unfortunately, Syrovatka" authorityYear="1991" box="[406,959,2013,2040]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis box="[406,423,2014,2039]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[438,506,2013,2039]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">pilosa</emphasis>
Loew. Unfortunately, 
<bibRefCitation author="Syrovatka, O." box="[763,959,2013,2039]" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" pagination="225 - 278" refId="ref8399" refString="Syrovatka, O. (1991) Revision of H. Loew's and T. Becker's types of Empis s. str. species (Diptera, Empididae) in the Berlin and St Petersburg Museums. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 67, 225 - 278. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnz. 19910670203" type="journal article" year="1991">Syrovátka (1991)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
omitted in his re-descriptions of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1340,1410,2014,2039]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[1340,1410,2014,2039]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="271">Empis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="272" pageId="5" pageNumber="271" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
characters such as the setosity of the prosternum. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1865" box="[744,874,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis box="[744,874,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">Empis hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the prosternum setose. The male terminalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1865" box="[151,237,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis box="[151,168,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[183,237,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[294,454,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropilosa">
<emphasis box="[294,311,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[326,454,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">nigropilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appear identical (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Collin, J. E." box="[713,907,189,215]" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" pagination="385 - 420" refId="ref7967" refString="Collin, J. E. (1960) Some Empididae from Palestine. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (13), 2, 385 - 420. [1959] https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222935908650872" type="journal article" year="1960">Collin 1960: 142</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 3; 
<bibRefCitation author="Syrovatka, O." box="[995,1234,188,215]" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" pagination="225 - 278" refId="ref8399" refString="Syrovatka, O. (1991) Revision of H. Loew's and T. Becker's types of Empis s. str. species (Diptera, Empididae) in the Berlin and St Petersburg Museums. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 67, 225 - 278. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnz. 19910670203" type="journal article" year="1991">Syrovátka 1991: 255</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 10A; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kustov, S. Yu. &amp; Shamshev, I. V." pageId="6" pageNumber="272" pagination="170 - 184" refId="ref8188" refString="Kustov, S. Yu. &amp; Shamshev, I. V. (2014) A review of dance-flies of the Empis (s. str.) pennipes group of species (Diptera: Empididae) from the Caucasus, with descriptions of five new species. Caucasian Entomological Bulletin, 10, 170 - 184. [in Russian, partly English] https: // doi. org / 10.23885 / 1814 - 3326 - 2014 - 10 - 1 - 170 - 184" type="journal article" year="2014">Kustov &amp; Shamshev 2014: 181</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 10) and the majority of other external characters match. However, 
<taxonomicName box="[1228,1388,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropilosa">
<emphasis box="[1228,1245,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1260,1388,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">nigropilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1865" box="[262,347,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis box="[262,279,262,287]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[293,347,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the bare prosternum (vs. setose), four scutellar setae (vs. 6–12), somewhat sparser and longer anteroventral setae on the hind femur and faintly infuscate wing (vs. brownish).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,153,539]" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">
It should be noted that some characters of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1865" box="[689,776,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis box="[689,706,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[722,776,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very variable, e.g., body size (
<quantity box="[1175,1316,332,359]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05" metricValueMax="5.6" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" unit="mm" value="5.05" valueMax="5.6" valueMin="4.5">4.5–5.6 mm</quantity>
, the lectotype— 
<quantity box="[228,316,368,395]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" unit="mm" value="5.6">5.6 mm</quantity>
); number of notopleural setae (3–5, usually 3–4, in the 
<typeStatus box="[925,1028,369,395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">lectotype</typeStatus>
4); number and robustness of scutellar setae (6–12, when 6 or 8 then 4 usually stronger); prosternum sometimes only with 1–3 setae on each side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,153,539]" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">
I provisionally retain 
<taxonomicName box="[441,600,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropilosa">
<emphasis box="[441,458,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[472,600,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="272">nigropilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a separate species until additional material becomes available from that region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
